Enums.name: AzureOpenAIServiceApiVersion
Enums.description: Known service API versions for Azure OpenAI.

properties.name: role
properties.description:
The role of the entity that is creating the message. Allowed values include:
- `user`: Indicates the message is sent by an actual user and should be used in most cases to represent user-generated messages.
- `assistant`: Indicates the message is generated by the assistant. Use this value to insert messages from the assistant into the conversation.

valueType.name: MessageContent
valueType.description: Represents a single piece of content in an Assistants API message.

properties.name: attachments
properties.description: A list of files attached to the message, and the tools they should be added to.

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: The ID of the file to attach to the message.

properties.name: tools
properties.description: The tools to add this file to.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of tool being defined: `file_search`

properties.name: file_search
properties.description: Overrides for the file search tool.

properties.name: max_num_results
properties.description:
The maximum number of results the file search tool should output. The default is 20 for `gpt-4*` models and 5 for `gpt-3.5-turbo`. This number should be between 1 and 50 inclusive.

Note that the file search tool may output fewer than `max_num_results` results. See the [file search tool documentation](/docs/assistants/tools/file-search#customizing-file-search-settings) for more information.

type.name: FileSearchRankingOptions
type.description:
The ranking options for the file search. If not specified, the file search tool will use the `auto` ranker and a score_threshold of 0.

See the [file search tool documentation](/docs/assistants/tools/file-search#customizing-file-search-settings) for more information.

properties.name: ranker
properties.description: The ranker to use for the file search. If not specified will use the `auto` ranker.

properties.name: score_threshold
properties.description: The score threshold for the file search. All values must be a floating point number between 0 and 1.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of tool being defined: `function`

properties.name: description
properties.description: A description of what the function does, used by the model to choose when and how to call the function.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to be called. Must be a-z, A-Z, 0-9, or contain underscores and dashes, with a maximum length of 64.

properties.name: parameters
properties.description:
The parameters the functions accepts, described as a JSON Schema object. See the [guide](/docs/guides/function-calling) for examples, and the [JSON Schema reference](https://json-schema.org/understanding-json-schema/) for documentation about the format.

Omitting `parameters` defines a function with an empty parameter list.

properties.name: strict
properties.description: Whether to enable strict schema adherence when generating the function call. If set to true, the model will follow the exact schema defined in the `parameters` field. Only a subset of JSON Schema is supported when `strict` is `true`. Learn more about Structured Outputs in the [function calling guide](docs/guides/function-calling).

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of tool being defined: `code_interpreter`

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of tool being defined: `file_search`

properties.name: metadata
properties.description:
Set of 16 key-value pairs that can be attached to an object. This can be
useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured
format, and querying for objects via API or the dashboard.

Keys are strings with a maximum length of 64 characters. Values are strings
with a maximum length of 512 characters.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The identifier, which can be referenced in API endpoints.

properties.name: object
properties.description: The object type, which is always `thread.message`.

properties.name: created_at
properties.description: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) for when the message was created.

properties.name: thread_id
properties.description: The [thread](/docs/api-reference/threads) ID that this message belongs to.

properties.name: status
properties.description: The status of the message, which can be either `in_progress`, `incomplete`, or `completed`.

properties.name: incomplete_details
properties.description: On an incomplete message, details about why the message is incomplete.

properties.name: reason
properties.description: The reason the message is incomplete.

properties.name: completed_at
properties.description: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) for when the message was completed.

properties.name: incomplete_at
properties.description: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) for when the message was marked as incomplete.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The entity that produced the message. One of `user` or `assistant`.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The content of the message in array of text and/or images.

properties.name: assistant_id
properties.description: If applicable, the ID of the [assistant](/docs/api-reference/assistants) that authored this message.

properties.name: run_id
properties.description: The ID of the [run](/docs/api-reference/runs) associated with the creation of this message. Value is `null` when messages are created manually using the create message or create thread endpoints.

properties.name: attachments
properties.description: A list of files attached to the message, and the tools they were added to.

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: The ID of the file to attach to the message.

properties.name: tools
properties.description: The tools to add this file to.

properties.name: metadata
properties.description:
Set of 16 key-value pairs that can be attached to an object. This can be
useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured
format, and querying for objects via API or the dashboard.

Keys are strings with a maximum length of 64 characters. Values are strings
with a maximum length of 512 characters.

properties.name: prompt
properties.description: A text description of the desired image(s). The maximum length is 1000 characters for `dall-e-2` and 4000 characters for `dall-e-3`.

properties.name: model
properties.description: The model to use for image generation.

properties.name: n
properties.description: The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10. For `dall-e-3`, only `n=1` is supported.

properties.name: quality
properties.description: The quality of the image that will be generated. `hd` creates images with finer details and greater consistency across the image. This param is only supported for `dall-e-3`.

properties.name: response_format
properties.description: The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of `url` or `b64_json`. URLs are only valid for 60 minutes after the image has been generated.

properties.name: size
properties.description: The size of the generated images. Must be one of `256x256`, `512x512`, or `1024x1024` for `dall-e-2`. Must be one of `1024x1024`, `1792x1024`, or `1024x1792` for `dall-e-3` models.

properties.name: style
properties.description: The style of the generated images. Must be one of `vivid` or `natural`. Vivid causes the model to lean towards generating hyper-real and dramatic images. Natural causes the model to produce more natural, less hyper-real looking images. This param is only supported for `dall-e-3`.

properties.name: user
properties.description: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse. [Learn more](/docs/guides/safety-best-practices#end-user-ids).

valueType.name: Image
valueType.description: Represents the url or the content of an image generated by the OpenAI API.

properties.name: b64_json
properties.description: The base64-encoded JSON of the generated image, if `response_format` is `b64_json`.

properties.name: url
properties.description: The URL of the generated image, if `response_format` is `url` (default).

properties.name: revised_prompt
properties.description: The prompt that was used to generate the image, if there was any revision to the prompt.

Models.name: AzureOpenAIDalleErrorResponse
Models.description: A structured representation of an error an Azure OpenAI request.

type.name: AzureOpenAIDalleError
type.description: The structured representation of an error from an Azure OpenAI image generation request.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The distinct, machine-generated identifier for the error.

properties.name: message
properties.description: A human-readable message associated with the error.

properties.name: param
properties.description: If applicable, the request input parameter associated with the error

properties.name: type
properties.description: If applicable, the input line number associated with the error.

properties.name: inner_error
properties.description: If applicable, an upstream error that originated this error.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The code associated with the inner error.

properties.name: revised_prompt
properties.description: If applicable, the modified prompt used for generation.

properties.name: content_filter_results
properties.description: The content filter result details associated with the inner error.

type.name: AzureContentFilterImagePromptResults
type.description: A content filter result for an image generation operation's input request content.

baseModel.name: AzureContentFilterImageResponseResults
baseModel.description: A content filter result for an image generation operation's output response content.

properties.name: sexual
properties.description:
A content filter category for language related to anatomical organs and genitals, romantic relationships, acts
portrayed in erotic or affectionate terms, pregnancy, physical sexual acts, including those portrayed as an
assault or a forced sexual violent act against one's will, prostitution, pornography, and abuse.

type.name: AzureContentFilterSeverityResult
type.description:
A labeled content filter result item that indicates whether the content was filtered and what the qualitative
severity level of the content was, as evaluated against content filter configuration for the category.

properties.name: filtered
properties.description: Whether the content severity resulted in a content filtering action.

properties.name: severity
properties.description: The labeled severity of the content.

properties.name: violence
properties.description:
A content filter category for language related to physical actions intended to hurt, injure, damage, or kill
someone or something; describes weapons, guns and related entities, such as manufactures, associations,
legislation, and so on.

properties.name: hate
properties.description:
A content filter category that can refer to any content that attacks or uses pejorative or discriminatory
language with reference to a person or identity group based on certain differentiating attributes of these groups
including but not limited to race, ethnicity, nationality, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation,
religion, immigration status, ability status, personal appearance, and body size.

properties.name: self_harm
properties.description:
A content filter category that describes language related to physical actions intended to purposely hurt, injure,
damage one's body or kill oneself.

properties.name: profanity
properties.description:
A detection result that identifies whether crude, vulgar, or otherwise objection language is present in the
content.

type.name: AzureContentFilterDetectionResult
type.description:
A labeled content filter result item that indicates whether the content was detected and whether the content was
filtered.

properties.name: filtered
properties.description: Whether the content detection resulted in a content filtering action.

properties.name: detected
properties.description: Whether the labeled content category was detected in the content.

properties.name: custom_blocklists
properties.description: A collection of binary filtering outcomes for configured custom blocklists.

type.name: AzureContentFilterBlocklistResult
type.description: A collection of true/false filtering results for configured custom blocklists.

properties.name: filtered
properties.description: A value indicating whether any of the detailed blocklists resulted in a filtering action.

properties.name: details
properties.description: The pairs of individual blocklist IDs and whether they resulted in a filtering action.

properties.name: filtered
properties.description: A value indicating whether the blocklist produced a filtering action.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The ID of the custom blocklist evaluated.

properties.name: jailbreak
properties.description:
A detection result that describes user prompt injection attacks, where malicious users deliberately exploit
system vulnerabilities to elicit unauthorized behavior from the LLM. This could lead to inappropriate content
generation or violations of system-imposed restrictions.

Models.name: AzureCreateChatCompletionRequest
Models.description:
The extended request model for chat completions against the Azure OpenAI service.
This adds the ability to provide data sources for the On Your Data feature.

properties.name: messages
properties.description:
A list of messages comprising the conversation so far. Depending on the
[model](/docs/models) you use, different message types (modalities) are
supported, like [text](/docs/guides/text-generation),
[images](/docs/guides/vision), and [audio](/docs/guides/audio).

discriminatorProperty.name: role
discriminatorProperty.description: The role of the author of this message.

system.name: ChatCompletionRequestSystemMessage
system.description:
Developer-provided instructions that the model should follow, regardless of
messages sent by the user. With o1 models and newer, use `developer` messages
for this purpose instead.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the system message.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the content part.

properties.name: text
properties.description: The text content.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `system`.

properties.name: name
properties.description: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

developer.name: ChatCompletionRequestDeveloperMessage
developer.description:
Developer-provided instructions that the model should follow, regardless of
messages sent by the user. With o1 models and newer, `developer` messages
replace the previous `system` messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the developer message.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `developer`.

properties.name: name
properties.description: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

user.name: ChatCompletionRequestUserMessage
user.description:
Messages sent by an end user, containing prompts or additional context
information.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the user message.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the content part.

properties.name: url
properties.description: Either a URL of the image or the base64 encoded image data.

properties.name: detail
properties.description: Specifies the detail level of the image. Learn more in the [Vision guide](/docs/guides/vision#low-or-high-fidelity-image-understanding).

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the content part. Always `input_audio`.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Base64 encoded audio data.

properties.name: format
properties.description: The format of the encoded audio data. Currently supports "wav" and "mp3".

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `user`.

properties.name: name
properties.description: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

assistant.name: ChatCompletionRequestAssistantMessage
assistant.description: Messages sent by the model in response to user messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the assistant message. Required unless `tool_calls` or `function_call` is specified.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the content part.

properties.name: refusal
properties.description: The refusal message generated by the model.

properties.name: refusal
properties.description: The refusal message by the assistant.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `assistant`.

properties.name: name
properties.description: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

properties.name: audio
properties.description:
Data about a previous audio response from the model.
[Learn more](/docs/guides/audio).

properties.name: id
properties.description: Unique identifier for a previous audio response from the model.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The ID of the tool call.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the tool. Currently, only `function` is supported.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The function that the model called.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to call.

properties.name: arguments
properties.description: The arguments to call the function with, as generated by the model in JSON format. Note that the model does not always generate valid JSON, and may hallucinate parameters not defined by your function schema. Validate the arguments in your code before calling your function.

properties.name: function_call
properties.description: Deprecated and replaced by `tool_calls`. The name and arguments of a function that should be called, as generated by the model.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `tool`.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the tool message.

properties.name: tool_call_id
properties.description: Tool call that this message is responding to.

function.name: ChatCompletionRequestFunctionMessage
function.deprecation: This field is marked as deprecated.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The role of the messages author, in this case `function`.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the function message.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to call.

properties.name: store
properties.description:
Whether or not to store the output of this chat completion request for
use in our [model distillation](/docs/guides/distillation) or
[evals](/docs/guides/evals) products.

properties.name: reasoning_effort
properties.description:
**o1 models only** 

Constrains effort on reasoning for 
[reasoning models](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/reasoning).
Currently supported values are `low`, `medium`, and `high`. Reducing
reasoning effort can result in faster responses and fewer tokens used
on reasoning in a response.

properties.name: metadata
properties.description:
Set of 16 key-value pairs that can be attached to an object. This can be
useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured
format, and querying for objects via API or the dashboard.

Keys are strings with a maximum length of 64 characters. Values are strings
with a maximum length of 512 characters.

properties.name: frequency_penalty
properties.description:
Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on
their existing frequency in the text so far, decreasing the model's
likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

properties.name: logit_bias
properties.description:
Modify the likelihood of specified tokens appearing in the completion.

Accepts a JSON object that maps tokens (specified by their token ID in the
tokenizer) to an associated bias value from -100 to 100. Mathematically,
the bias is added to the logits generated by the model prior to sampling.
The exact effect will vary per model, but values between -1 and 1 should
decrease or increase likelihood of selection; values like -100 or 100
should result in a ban or exclusive selection of the relevant token.

properties.name: logprobs
properties.description:
Whether to return log probabilities of the output tokens or not. If true,
returns the log probabilities of each output token returned in the
`content` of `message`.

properties.name: top_logprobs
properties.description:
An integer between 0 and 20 specifying the number of most likely tokens to
return at each token position, each with an associated log probability.
`logprobs` must be set to `true` if this parameter is used.

properties.name: max_tokens
properties.description:
The maximum number of [tokens](/tokenizer) that can be generated in the
chat completion. This value can be used to control
[costs](https://openai.com/api/pricing/) for text generated via API.

This value is now deprecated in favor of `max_completion_tokens`, and is
not compatible with [o1 series models](/docs/guides/reasoning).

properties.name: max_completion_tokens
properties.description: An upper bound for the number of tokens that can be generated for a completion, including visible output tokens and [reasoning tokens](/docs/guides/reasoning).

properties.name: n
properties.description: How many chat completion choices to generate for each input message. Note that you will be charged based on the number of generated tokens across all of the choices. Keep `n` as `1` to minimize costs.

properties.name: prediction
properties.description:
Configuration for a [Predicted Output](/docs/guides/predicted-outputs),
which can greatly improve response times when large parts of the model
response are known ahead of time. This is most common when you are
regenerating a file with only minor changes to most of the content.

type.name: ChatOutputPrediction
type.description: Base representation of predicted output from a model.

content.name: ChatOutputPredictionContent
content.description:
Static predicted output content, such as the content of a text file that is
being regenerated.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
The type of the predicted content you want to provide. This type is
currently always `content`.

properties.name: content
properties.description:
The content that should be matched when generating a model response.
If generated tokens would match this content, the entire model response
can be returned much more quickly.

properties.name: audio
properties.description:
Parameters for audio output. Required when audio output is requested with
`modalities: ["audio"]`. [Learn more](/docs/guides/audio).

properties.name: voice
properties.description: The voice the model uses to respond. Supported voices are `ash`, `ballad`, `coral`, `sage`, and `verse` (also supported but not recommended are `alloy`, `echo`, and `shimmer`; these voices are less expressive).

properties.name: format
properties.description:
Specifies the output audio format. Must be one of `wav`, `mp3`, `flac`,
`opus`, or `pcm16`.

properties.name: presence_penalty
properties.description:
Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on
whether they appear in the text so far, increasing the model's likelihood
to talk about new topics.

properties.name: response_format
properties.description:
An object specifying the format that the model must output.

Setting to `{ "type": "json_schema", "json_schema": {...} }` enables
Structured Outputs which ensures the model will match your supplied JSON
schema. Learn more in the [Structured Outputs
guide](/docs/guides/structured-outputs).

Setting to `{ "type": "json_object" }` enables JSON mode, which ensures
the message the model generates is valid JSON.

**Important:** when using JSON mode, you **must** also instruct the model
to produce JSON yourself via a system or user message. Without this, the
model may generate an unending stream of whitespace until the generation
reaches the token limit, resulting in a long-running and seemingly "stuck"
request. Also note that the message content may be partially cut off if
`finish_reason="length"`, which indicates the generation exceeded
`max_tokens` or the conversation exceeded the max context length.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of response format being defined: `text`

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of response format being defined: `json_object`

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of response format being defined: `json_schema`

properties.name: description
properties.description: A description of what the response format is for, used by the model to determine how to respond in the format.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the response format. Must be a-z, A-Z, 0-9, or contain underscores and dashes, with a maximum length of 64.

type.name: ResponseFormatJsonSchemaSchema
type.description: The schema for the response format, described as a JSON Schema object.

properties.name: strict
properties.description: Whether to enable strict schema adherence when generating the output. If set to true, the model will always follow the exact schema defined in the `schema` field. Only a subset of JSON Schema is supported when `strict` is `true`. To learn more, read the [Structured Outputs guide](/docs/guides/structured-outputs).

properties.name: seed
properties.description:
This feature is in Beta.
If specified, our system will make a best effort to sample deterministically, such that repeated requests with the same `seed` and parameters should return the same result.
Determinism is not guaranteed, and you should refer to the `system_fingerprint` response parameter to monitor changes in the backend.

properties.name: stop
properties.description: Up to 4 sequences where the API will stop generating further tokens.

properties.name: stream
properties.description: If set, partial message deltas will be sent, like in ChatGPT. Tokens will be sent as data-only [server-sent events](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events/Using_server-sent_events#Event_stream_format) as they become available, with the stream terminated by a `data: [DONE]` message. [Example Python code](https://cookbook.openai.com/examples/how_to_stream_completions).

type.name: ChatCompletionStreamOptions
type.description: Options for streaming response. Only set this when you set `stream: true`.

properties.name: include_usage
properties.description: If set, an additional chunk will be streamed before the `data: [DONE]` message. The `usage` field on this chunk shows the token usage statistics for the entire request, and the `choices` field will always be an empty array. All other chunks will also include a `usage` field, but with a null value.

properties.name: temperature
properties.description:
What sampling temperature to use, between 0 and 2. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic.
We generally recommend altering this or `top_p` but not both.

properties.name: top_p
properties.description:
An alternative to sampling with temperature, called nucleus sampling,
where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability
mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass
are considered.

We generally recommend altering this or `temperature` but not both.

properties.name: tools
properties.description: A list of tools the model may call. Currently, only functions are supported as a tool. Use this to provide a list of functions the model may generate JSON inputs for. A max of 128 functions are supported.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the tool. Currently, only `function` is supported.

variantTypes.name: ChatCompletionNamedToolChoice
variantTypes.description: Specifies a tool the model should use. Use to force the model to call a specific function.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the tool. Currently, only `function` is supported.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to call.

properties.name: user
properties.description: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse. [Learn more](/docs/guides/safety-best-practices#end-user-ids).

properties.name: function_call
properties.description:
Deprecated in favor of `tool_choice`.

Controls which (if any) function is called by the model.

`none` means the model will not call a function and instead generates a
message.

`auto` means the model can pick between generating a message or calling a
function.

Specifying a particular function via `{"name": "my_function"}` forces the
model to call that function.

`none` is the default when no functions are present. `auto` is the default
if functions are present.

variantTypes.name: ChatCompletionFunctionCallOption
variantTypes.description: Specifying a particular function via `{"name": "my_function"}` forces the model to call that function.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to call.

properties.name: functions
properties.description:
Deprecated in favor of `tools`.

A list of functions the model may generate JSON inputs for.

valueType.name: ChatCompletionFunctions
valueType.deprecation: This field is marked as deprecated.

properties.name: description
properties.description: A description of what the function does, used by the model to choose when and how to call the function.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to be called. Must be a-z, A-Z, 0-9, or contain underscores and dashes, with a maximum length of 64.

properties.name: parameters
properties.description:
The parameters the functions accepts, described as a JSON Schema object. See the [guide](/docs/guides/function-calling) for examples, and the [JSON Schema reference](https://json-schema.org/understanding-json-schema/) for documentation about the format.

Omitting `parameters` defines a function with an empty parameter list.

properties.name: data_sources
properties.description: The data sources to use for the On Your Data feature, exclusive to Azure OpenAI.

valueType.name: AzureChatDataSource
valueType.description:
A representation of configuration data for a single Azure OpenAI chat data source.
This will be used by a chat completions request that should use Azure OpenAI chat extensions to augment the
response behavior.
The use of this configuration is compatible only with Azure OpenAI.

discriminatorProperty.name: type
discriminatorProperty.description: The differentiating type identifier for the data source.

azure_search.name: AzureSearchChatDataSource
azure_search.description: Represents a data source configuration that will use an Azure Search resource.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The discriminated type identifier, which is always 'azure_search'.

properties.name: parameters
properties.description: The parameter information to control the use of the Azure Search data source.

properties.name: top_n_documents
properties.description: The configured number of documents to feature in the query.

properties.name: in_scope
properties.description: Whether queries should be restricted to use of the indexed data.

properties.name: strictness
properties.description:
The configured strictness of the search relevance filtering.
Higher strictness will increase precision but lower recall of the answer.

properties.name: max_search_queries
properties.description:
The maximum number of rewritten queries that should be sent to the search provider for a single user message.
By default, the system will make an automatic determination.

properties.name: allow_partial_result
properties.description:
If set to true, the system will allow partial search results to be used and the request will fail if all
partial queries fail. If not specified or specified as false, the request will fail if any search query fails.

properties.name: include_contexts
properties.description:
The output context properties to include on the response.
By default, citations and intent will be requested.

properties.name: endpoint
properties.description: The absolute endpoint path for the Azure Search resource to use.

properties.name: index_name
properties.description: The name of the index to use, as specified in the Azure Search resource.

properties.name: authentication
properties.description: The authentication mechanism to use with Azure Search.

properties.name: fields_mapping
properties.description: The field mappings to use with the Azure Search resource.

Can be used in conjunction with the `seed` request parameter to understand when backend changes have been made that might impact determinism.

properties.description: The object type, which is always `chat.completion`.

properties.description: Number of tokens in the prompt.

properties.description: Total number of tokens used in the request (prompt + completion).

properties.description:
When using Predicted Outputs, the number of tokens in the
prediction that appeared in the completion.

properties.description: Audio input tokens generated by the model.

properties.name: reasoning_tokens
properties.description: Tokens generated by the model for reasoning.

properties.name: rejected_prediction_tokens
properties.description:
When using Predicted Outputs, the number of tokens in the
prediction that did not appear in the completion. However, like
reasoning tokens, these tokens are still counted in the total
completion tokens for purposes of billing, output, and context window
limits.

properties.name: prompt_tokens_details
properties.description: Breakdown of tokens used in the prompt.

properties.name: audio_tokens
properties.description: Audio input tokens present in the prompt.

properties.name: cached_tokens
properties.description: Cached tokens present in the prompt.

properties.name: finish_reason
properties.description:
The reason the model stopped generating tokens. This will be `stop` if the model hit a natural stop point or a provided stop sequence,
`length` if the maximum number of tokens specified in the request was reached,
`content_filter` if content was omitted due to a flag from our content filters,
`tool_calls` if the model called a tool, or `function_call` (deprecated) if the model called a function.

properties.name: index
properties.description: The index of the choice in the list of choices.

properties.name: expires_at
properties.description:
The Unix timestamp (in seconds) for when this audio response will
no longer be accessible on the server for use in multi-turn
conversations.

properties.name: data
properties.description:
Base64 encoded audio bytes generated by the model, in the format
specified in the request.

properties.name: transcript
properties.description: Transcript of the audio generated by the model.

properties.name: logprobs
properties.description: Log probability information for the choice.

properties.description: A list of message content tokens with log probability information.

properties.name: token
properties.description: The token.

properties.description: The log probability of this token, if it is within the top 20 most likely tokens. Otherwise, the value `-9999.0` is used to signify that the token is very unlikely.

properties.name: bytes
properties.description: A list of integers representing the UTF-8 bytes representation of the token. Useful in instances where characters are represented by multiple tokens and their byte representations must be combined to generate the correct text representation. Can be `null` if there is no bytes representation for the token.

properties.name: top_logprobs
properties.description: List of the most likely tokens and their log probability, at this token position. In rare cases, there may be fewer than the number of requested `top_logprobs` returned.

portrayed in erotic or affectionate terms, pregnancy, physical sexual acts, including those portrayed as an
assault or a forced sexual violent act against one's will, prostitution, pornography, and abuse.

A content filter category that can refer to any content that attacks or uses pejorative or discriminatory
language with reference to a person or identity group based on certain differentiating attributes of these groups
including but not limited to race, ethnicity, nationality, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation,
religion, immigration status, ability status, personal appearance, and body size.
